      "text": "EIA sees 2024 US wholesale electricity prices close to or lower than last year | Reuters\nSkip to main content\nExclusive news, data and analytics for financial market professionalsLearn more aboutRefinitiv\n\n\nMy News\nRegister\n# EIA sees 2024 US wholesale electricity prices close to or lower than last year\nByReuters\nJanuary 18, 20243:20 PM UTCUpdated ago\nText\n* Small Text\n* Medium Text\n* Large Text\nShare\n* X\n* Facebook\n* Linkedin\n* Email\n* Link\nPeople react to a period of hot weather in Houston\nA general view of electric lines as demand for power surges during a period of hot weather in Houston, Texas, U.S. June 27, 2023. REUTERS/Callaghan O’Hare/File Photo/File PhotoPurchase LicensingRights, opens new tab\n* Companies\n* \nU.S. Energy Information Administration\n\nFollow\nJan 18 (Reuters) - Wholesale electricity prices for 2024 in most areas of the U.S. are seen to be close to or slightly lower than in 2023, because of relatively stable generation fuel costs, the U.S. Energy Information Admini",
