ons. MISO has resolved 90 of these, including six in 2024. As recommendations differ in complexity and impact, MISO can quicklyresolve some, while others require much more time and effort or are contingent on technological advancement. Collaboration with the IMM led to enhancements that closed out recommendationsrelated to resource accreditation, demand resources, and shortage pricing in the energy and operating reserve markets. Additionally, MISO has made progress on several other IMMrecommendations, including ones related to the Look Ahead Commitment Tool, unit commitments, operator logging and incentives to generators to improve setpoint following.In the attached detailed narrative response, you will find the following: • MISO’s underlying rationale for each response is based on detailed assessments of dataand analysis provided by the IMM and relevant context assembled by MISO. In some instances, MISO and the IMM have agreed to spend additional time exploring the priority  ...   We look forward to reviewing our responses and progress on the IMM’s recommendations. 2024 State of the Market (SOM) Report RecommendationsNew (2024) Recommendation Responses.................................................................................................12024-1: Modify RDT demand curve steps and RPE binding limits.............................................2 2024-2: Shift a large share of transmission capability from the annual ARR allocationand FTR auction to seasonal and monthly auctions..........................................................................32024-3: Limit acceptance of transferred M2M flowgates to those where MISO has more effective relief and require proper use of the relief request software..........................42024-4: Improve constraint management and dead bus criteria for Forced Off Asset"
