        "FROM: ZAK JOUNDI, EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR MARKETS AND GRID STRATEGY SUBJECT: MISO’S RESPONSE TO THE IMM 2024 STATE OF THE MARKET REPORTPlease find attached MISO’s response to the annual 2024 State of the Market (SOM) Report by the Independent Market Monitor, which Dr. Patton reviewed with you in June.The report concluded that MISO’s energy and ancillary services markets performed competitively in 2024. The IMM made four new recommendations to enhance the markets.MISO agrees with all four issues identified by the IMM and the recommended solution for one with the other three pendingfurther evaluation. MISO is actively working on one of the four recommendations and plans to work on the other three within the next five years.MISO and the IMM continue to find ways to work collaboratively through the stakeholder process on these recommendations to drive valueMISO is providing two forms of response: 1) a summary presentation for the planned discussion with the Markets Committee of the Board of Directors on December 9, and 2) a narrativedescription, which provides a more detailed response to each recommendation, and follows this MISO continues to leverage the nomenclature used in prior responses that highlight theanticipated timeline for resolving individual recommendations. The “MISO Five-Year Action” • Active: MISO has given these recommendations a high priority and is actively working on• Planned: MISO is not currently working on these recommendations but has prioritized • Deferred: MISO has deemed these recommendations are a lower priority and will not bepursuing them in the current five-year planning process • Disagree: MISO disagrees with this recommendation Of the 34 recommendations, fifteen are Active, eleven are Planned, eight are Deferred.The following chart breaks down these totals into the four IMM categories. With this year’s four new recommendations, the IMM has made a total of 124 recommendationsover the last 20 years to improve MISO’s markets and operations. MISO has resolved 90 of these, including six in 2024. As recommendations differ in complexity and impact, MISO can quicklyresolve some, while others require much more time and effort or are contingent on technological advancement. Collaboration with the IMM led to enhancements that closed out recommendationsrelated to resource accreditation, demand resources, and shortage pricing in the energy and operating reserve markets. Additionally, MISO has made progress on several other IMMrecommendations, including ones related to the Look Ahead Commitment Tool, unit commitments, operator logging and incentives to generators to improve setpoint following.In the attached detailed narrative response, you will find the following: • MISO’s underlying rationale for each response is based on detailed assessments of dataand analysis provided by the IMM and relevant context assembled by MISO. In some instances, MISO and the IMM have agreed to spend additional time exploring the priority  ...   We look forward to reviewing our responses and progress on the IMM’s recommendations. 2024 State of the Market (SOM) Report RecommendationsNew (2024) Recommendation Responses.................................................................................................12024-1: Modify RDT demand curve steps and RPE binding limits.............................................2 2024-2: Shift a large share of transmission capability from the annual ARR allocationand FTR auction to seasonal and monthly auctions..........................................................................32024-3: Limit acceptance of transferred M2M flowgates to those where MISO has more effective relief and require proper use of the relief request software..........................42024-4: Improve constraint management and dead bus criteria for Forced Off Asset"
